children.text: There are plaster ceiling butt joints that have been installed on/near the truss.
The Victorian Building Authority’s Guide to Standards and Tolerances states in section 9.11 Plasterboard Sheeting, that
‘The installation and jointing of plasterboard sheeting systems is defective if it does not conform to AS/NZS 2589 and the manufacturer’s installation instructions’ .
The wall sheet manufacturer’s installation manual states

‘If sheets must be joined ‘end-to-end’ then the joints must fall mid-span between framing members and be supported by back-blocking panels (nom 400mm wide) for the length of the joint or between stitching battens’ .
The builder must replace the affected ceiling sheets, ensuring that any required butt joints occur mid-span between the framing members.
